etter]] of Belgian bishops deprecates Catholic membership of masonic lodges.{{r|Kroniek|p=628}}\n|-\n| [[1838 in Belgium|1838]] || || [[Hendrik Conscience]]'s ''[[The Lion of Flanders (novel)|De Leeuw van Vlaenderen]]'' published.\n|-\n| [[1839 in Belgium|1839]] || 4 February || The Kingdom of the Netherlands recognises Belgian independence.<ref name=\"William Henry Overall 1870 p. 76\"/>\n|-\n| || 19 April || [[Treaty of London (1839)|Treaty of London]] signed, finalising international guarantees of Belgian independence and neutrality.<ref name=Irving>[[Joseph Irving]], ''The Annals of Our Time'' (London and New York, 1871).</ref>{{rp|39}}\n|-\n| [[1840 in Belgium|1840]] || 18 April || [[Joseph Lebeau]] replaces [[Barth\u00e9l\u00e9my de Theux de Meylandt]] as Prime Minister \n|-\n| [[1841 in Belgium|1841]] || 13 April || [[Jean-Baptiste Nothomb]] replaces [[Joseph Lebeau]] as Prime Minister\n|-\n| [[1845 in Belgium|1845]] || 30 July || [[Sylvain Van de Weyer]] replaces [[Jean-Baptiste Nothomb]] as Prime Minister\n|-\n| [[1846 in Belgium|1846]] || 31 March || [[Barth\u00e9l\u00e9my de Theux de Meylandt]] replaces [[Sylvain Van de Weyer]] as Prime Minister\n|-\n| [[1847 in Belgium|1847]] || 12 August || [[Charles Rogier]] replaces [[Barth\u00e9l\u00e9my de Theux de Meylandt]] as Prime Minister \n|-\n| [[1848 in Belgium|1848]] || 1 April || French Republican agitators seeking to foment revolution in Belgium arrested at [[Qui\u00e9vrain]].{{r|Irving|p=244}}\n|-\n| || 13 June || [[Belgian general election, 1848]]\n|-\n| [[1850 in Belgium|1850]] || 5 May || [[National Bank of Belgium]] founded\n|-\n| || 11 June || [[1850 Belgian general election|Partial legislative elections]]\n|-\n| [[1851 in Belgium|1851]] || 27 October || Commercial treaty between Belgium and the United Kingdom concluded in London.{{r|Irving|p=338}}<ref>C. Pety de Thoz\u00e9e, ''Syst\u00e8me commercial de la Belgique'', vol. 2 (Brussels, Bruylant-Christophe, 1875), pp. 76-80. [https://books.google.co