ber || [[Siege of Grave (1602)|Siege of Grave]]\n|-\n| || September || [[Mutiny of Hoogstraten]] begins.\n|-\n| || November || Military engineer [[Pompeo Targone]] arrives in the camp before Ostend.<ref>Werner Thomas, \"Het beleg van Oostende\", in ''De val van het Nieuwe Troje: Het beleg van Oostende, 1601\u20131604'', ed. Werner Thomas (Ostend and Leuven, 2004), p. 94.</ref>\n|-\n| [[1603 in Belgium|1603]] || 26 May || [[Federico Spinola]] dies in the [[Battle of Sluis (1603)|Battle of Sluis]].<ref>Werner Thomas, \"Het beleg van Oostende\", in ''De val van het Nieuwe Troje: Het beleg van Oostende, 1601\u20131604'', ed. Werner Thomas (Ostend and Leuven, 2004), p. 96.</ref>\n|-\n| || October || [[Ambrogio Spinola]] appointed commander-in-chief of the army besieging Ostend.<ref>Werner Thomas, \"Het beleg van Oostende\", in ''De val van het Nieuwe Troje: Het beleg van Oostende, 1601\u20131604'', ed. Werner Thomas (Ostend and Leuven, 2004), p. 97.</ref>\n|-\n| [[1604 in Belgium|1604]] || 19 May || [[Maurice, Prince of Orange|Maurice of Nassau]] [[Siege of Sluis (1604)|lays siege to Sluis]].<ref>Werner Thomas, \"Het beleg van Oostende\", in ''De val van het Nieuwe Troje: Het beleg van Oostende, 1601\u20131604'', ed. Werner Thomas (Ostend and Leuven, 2004), p. 98.</ref>\n|-\n| || 20 September || Negotiations for the surrender of Ostend begin.<ref name=\"Werner Thomas 2004 p. 99\">Werner Thomas, \"Het beleg van Oostende\", in ''De val van het Nieuwe Troje: Het beleg van Oostende, 1601\u20131604'', ed. Werner Thomas (Ostend and Leuven, 2004), p. 99.</ref>\n|-\n| || 22 September || [[Siege of Ostend]] concludes.<ref name=\"Werner Thomas 2004 p. 99\"/>\n|-\n| [[1605 in Belgium|1605]] || 17 May || Don [[\u00cd\u00f1igo de Borja]] repulses attempted Dutch landing at Blokkersdijk, near Antwerp.<ref>Paul Arblaster, ''From Ghent to Aix: How They Brought the News in the Habsburg Netherlands'' (Leiden and Boston, 2014), pp. 83\u201384. [https://books.google.com/books?isbn=900427684